pi commands:

1.htop - show performance.

2.cd - go to to directory.

3.sudo modprobe bcm2835-v4l2 - make the pi camera as usb camera.

4.raspistill -o output.jpg - take a photo from camera but from pi camera.

5.ifconfig - show the ip of the raspberry.

6.vcgencmd get_camera - show if raspberry camera is detected.

7./opt/vc/bin/vcgencmd measure_temp - show the Temperature of the cpu in the raspberry, the max temperature need to be around 80c. 

